# Supabase Database Schema

Schema files live in `supabase/`:

- `supabase/reset.sql` – selective wipe script (run first when resetting experiment data; preserves user tables)
- `supabase/schema.sql` – table/view definitions (run first)
- `supabase/rls_policies.sql` – Row Level Security policies (run second)

The daily cron job is at `src/app/api/cron/daily/route.ts` (runs every weekday; AI ratings + portfolio only execute on rebalance day, prices saved daily).
The AI prompt template and JSON schema are at `src/lib/aiPrompt.ts`.

## Versioning

All strategy identity/version configuration derives from two files:
- `src/lib/ai-strategy-registry.ts` — master registry of all AIT strategy entries (aitCode, robotName, slug, appVersion, prompt, model, universe, defaultPortfolio).
- `src/lib/strategyConfig.ts` — derives `STRATEGY_CONFIG` and `APP_VERSION` from the active registry entry (`ACTIVE_STRATEGY_ENTRY`).

Single strategy lineage axis:

- `APP_VERSION` (semver, e.g. `v1.0.1`) — sole lineage axis. Bump for all changes: prompt text, model, portfolio rules, universe, ranking, etc.
- `STRATEGY_CONFIG` re-exports from the registry: canonical slug (`ait-1-daneel`), display name, aitCode, robotName, prompt, model, and defaultPortfolio construction params.
- `GIT_COMMIT_SHA` captures the deploy commit (from `VERCEL_GIT_COMMIT_SHA`) stored in `ai_run_batches.git_commit_sha`.
- **Cron mismatch guard** (structural params only): throws if `index_name`, `rebalance_frequency`, `portfolio_size`, `weighting_method`, or `transaction_cost_bps` differ for the existing slug. Non-structural changes (`version`, `prompt_id`, `model_id`, `name`, `description`) are updated in-place.
- `MODEL_VERSION` is **removed**. All changes (prompt, model, portfolio rules) use `APP_VERSION`.

**Important**: When modifying `src/lib/aiPrompt.ts` or the AI model/prompt settings, bump `appVersion` in the active registry entry in `src/lib/ai-strategy-registry.ts` (which automatically bumps `APP_VERSION`). To create a new strategy lineage, add a new entry to `AI_STRATEGIES` with a new `aitCode` and `slug`.

Important: if you suggest changes to supabase/schema.sql, you must also suggest an SQL editor function to implement those changes in supabase.

You must also keep this file up to date.

## Two-layer Architecture

- **Layer A (AI rating model)**: `strategy_models` defines the AI strategy (prompt, model, universe, tracking portfolio). This is the rating engine.
- **Layer B (portfolio construction)**: `portfolio_construction_configs` defines how a portfolio is built from the ratings (risk level, rebalance frequency, weighting, top_n). Users configure this layer independently.

## Tables (6 layers)

**Reference data**: `stocks`, `ai_prompts`, `ai_models`.

**NASDAQ-100 membership**: `nasdaq100_snapshots`, `nasdaq100_snapshot_stocks`, `nasdaq_100_daily_raw`.

**Strategy/version control (Layer A)**: `strategy_models` (canonical slug + AIT identity fields `ait_code` + `robot_name`; structural params define the rating engine; no `unique(name, version)` — slug is the sole identity), `ai_run_batches`, `ai_analysis_runs`.

**Model-layer performance + research**: `strategy_portfolio_holdings`, `strategy_rebalance_actions`, `strategy_performance_weekly`, `strategy_quintile_returns`, `strategy_cross_sectional_regressions`.

**Portfolio construction layer (Layer B)**: `portfolio_construction_configs` (risk 1-6 × weekly/monthly/quarterly/yearly × equal/cap; seeded with 26 standard configs; default = risk 3 / weekly / equal), `strategy_portfolio_config_performance` (config-scoped performance rows keyed by strategy_id + config_id + run_date; includes `strategy_status` (in_progress/active), `compute_status` (pending/ready/failed)), `portfolio_config_compute_queue` (on-demand compute queue for non-precomputed configs; service role only).

**User portfolio tables**: `user_portfolio_profiles` (active profiles per user; stores `config_id`, `investment_size`, `user_start_date`, `notifications_enabled` — separate from model-level performance), `user_portfolio_positions` (holdings snapshot per profile), plus existing `user_portfolio_stocks` (watchlist/saved holdings).

**Frontend-facing**: `nasdaq100_recommendations_current`, views `nasdaq100_scores_7d_view`, `nasdaq100_current_members`, `nasdaq100_latest_snapshot`.

**User account tables**: `user_profiles`, `newsletter_subscribers`.

## Key conventions

- All PKs are UUID (`gen_random_uuid()`).
- The cron job uses `createAdminClient()` (service role key), bypassing RLS.
- Frontend reads use anon/authenticated key with RLS policies.
- Cron precomputes: risk 1-6 × weekly+monthly × equal + risk-3 × weekly+monthly × cap. All other configs use on-demand async compute.
- **Model performance vs. user performance are always separate**: `strategy_performance_weekly` and `strategy_portfolio_config_performance` track the strategy since inception; `user_portfolio_profiles.user_start_date` tracks the user's entry point.
- When modifying the schema, update `supabase/schema.sql`, `supabase/rls_policies.sql`, the cron job, and this rule file.
- When modifying strategy parameters, prompt, model, or portfolio rules, bump `appVersion` in the active `AI_STRATEGIES` entry in `src/lib/ai-strategy-registry.ts`.
- SQL helper functions: `public.backfill_portfolio_config_mappings()` (backfills default config performance from weekly data), `public.verify_strategy_model_migration()` (validates FK integrity and slug uniqueness).
